\title{<%=title%>}
\author{<%=authors%>}
\date{<%=date%>}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

\begin{abstract}
<%=getDescription(pkg)%>
\end{abstract}

\section{Introduction}

To load the package, do
\begin{verbatim}
library(<%=getName(pkg)%>)
\end{verbatim}
This will also load all required packages, display the version number of the <%=getName(pkg)%> package, and explain how to access its help pages.\\

\subsection{RSP main menu}
To launch the RSP main menu in the default web browser, do
\begin{verbatim}
browseRsp()
\end{verbatim}
If not already started, this will also start the internal R web server, through which the RSP pages are processed.  To stop the internal web server, do
\begin{verbatim}
browseRsp(stop=TRUE)
\end{verbatim}

\subsection{Further information}
For further information, such as translating and processing RSP files, see the RSP sections in the RSP main menu.


